# Complete POS System — Module Overview

A modern retail POS system has these core areas. I've organized them by **priority** so you can plan what to build first.

---

## 🔴 Tier 1 — Core (Must Have)

### 1. New Sale (✅ Already Built)
- Barcode scanning / product search
- Cart management (add, remove, quantity, per-item discount)
- Live totals (subtotal, discount, tax, grand total)

### 2. Checkout / Tender
- **Order Summary** — final review of cart before payment
- **Global Discount** — flat % or fixed amount off the entire order
- **Alliance/Promo Discount** — pre-configured discount programs from a master list
- **Tender Types:**
  - 💵 **Cash** — amount tendered, change due calculation
  - 💳 **Card** — reference number capture
  - 🔀 **Partial/Split** — part cash + part card (amounts must equal total)
- **Receipt Generation** — print or email receipt after sale

### 3. Sales History / Orders
- List of completed orders (filterable by date, cashier, terminal)
- Order detail view (items, discounts, payment method)
- **Void/Cancel** an order (with reason, manager approval)
- **Return/Refund** — select items from a past order to return

### 4. Cash Management
- **Opening Balance** — cashier declares starting cash at shift start
- **Cash Drop** — mid-shift cash removal to safe (recorded)
- **Cash Pickup** — manager collects cash
- **Closing/End of Day (EOD)** — cashier counts register, system compares expected vs actual
- **Over/Short Report** — discrepancy tracking

---

## 🟡 Tier 2 — Important

### 5. Customer Management
- Quick customer lookup (phone, loyalty card, name)
- Attach customer to a sale for tracking
- Customer purchase history
- **Loyalty Points** — earn on purchase, redeem as discount

### 6. Hold / Recall Sale
- **Hold** — park a half-done sale (customer forgot wallet, etc.)
- **Recall** — bring back a held sale to resume checkout
- Multiple holds per terminal

### 7. Discount & Promotion Master
- **Alliance Discounts** — company-wide agreements (e.g., 10% for partner employees)
- **Promo Campaigns** — buy-2-get-1, seasonal %, bundle deals
- **Coupon Codes** — one-time or multi-use codes
- **Employee Discount** — automatic for staff purchases

### 8. Inventory at POS
- Real-time stock display per item (already showing In/Out)
- **Stock Receive** — accept delivery at the store level
- **Stock Transfer Request** — request items from warehouse
- **Stock Count / Audit** — periodic physical count

### 9. Exchange
- Customer brings back Item A, swaps for Item B
- System handles the price difference (customer pays extra or gets credit)

---

## 🟢 Tier 3 — Nice to Have

### 10. Reports & Analytics
| Report | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| Daily Sales Summary | Total sales, voids, returns, by tender type |
| Hourly Sales | Sales volume by hour (peak analysis) |
| Cashier Performance | Sales per cashier, avg transaction value |
| Top Selling Items | Best sellers by quantity and revenue |
| Discount Report | Total discounts given, by type |
| Tax Report | Tax collected breakdown |
| Stock Movement | Items sold vs received vs transferred |
| Cash Drawer Report | Open/close/drop/pickup log |

### 11. Multi-Terminal Management
- Terminal status dashboard (online/offline)
- Remote terminal configuration
- Terminal-specific receipt headers

### 12. Gift Cards
- Sell and activate gift cards
- Redeem gift card balance at checkout
- Balance inquiry

### 13. Layaway
- Customer pays in installments
- Items reserved until fully paid
- Payment schedule tracking

### 14. Price Override
- Manager can override item price at POS (with reason + auth)
- Audit trail for all price overrides

---

## 🗺 Recommended Build Order

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Phase 1 - NOW] --> B[Checkout / Tender Page]
    A --> C[Sales History + Void]
    B --> D[Phase 2]
    C --> D
    D --> E[Cash Management - Open/Close/Drop]
    D --> F[Hold / Recall Sale]
    D --> G[Discount & Promo Master]
    E --> H[Phase 3]
    F --> H
    G --> H
    H --> I[Customer + Loyalty]
    H --> J[Returns / Exchange]
    H --> K[Reports Dashboard]
    K --> L[Phase 4]
    I --> L
    J --> L
    L --> M[Gift Cards]
    L --> N[Layaway]
    L --> O[Price Override]
```

